  "prompt": "What is securities market and what are the different types?",
  "response": "The securities market is a platform where financial instruments like stocks, bonds, and other securities are bought and sold. Here are the different types of securities markets:\n\n1. Primary Market\n- First-time issuance of securities\n- Companies raise capital through Initial Public Offerings (IPOs)\n- Initial sale of stocks or bonds directly to investors\n\n2. Secondary Market\n- Trading of previously issued securities\n- Includes stock exchanges like NYSE and NASDAQ\n- Allows investors to buy and sell existing securities\n\n3. Stock Market\n- Trading of company shares\n- Divided into equity markets\n- Provides companies with capital and investors with ownership\n\n4. Bond Market\n- Trading of debt securities\n- Government and corporate bonds\n- Fixed income investments with predetermined interest rates\n\n5. Money Market\n- Short-term debt instruments\n- Highly liquid securities\n- Includes Treasury bills, commercial paper, certificates of deposit\n\n6. Derivative Market\n- Contracts deriving value from underlying assets\n- Includes futures, options, swaps\n- Used for hedging and speculation\n\n7. Commodity Market\n- Trading of raw materials and primary agricultural products\n- Includes metals, energy, agricultural goods\n- Futures and spot markets\n\n8. Foreign Exchange (Forex) Market\n- Currency trading\n- International currency exchange\n- Largest financial market globally",
